## Never Idle

There are NO diminishing returns. Work is infinite:
- Stress testing is ALWAYS valuable — generate harder adversarial tests every tick
- Test hardening is ALWAYS possible — there's always a harder test to write
- Code quality can ALWAYS improve — fewer type holes, less dead code, cleaner architecture
- Research reveals ALWAYS more — competitors, best practices, industry trends

**When you feel stuck: launch 20 explorer agents.** They will find work. There is always something to improve. Do not stop. Do not say "diminishing returns." The loop runs until the operator tells it to stop.

**DO NOT generate fake improvement.** Every change must be genuinely better than before. Generating tests for impossible edge cases is fake. Refactoring already-clean code is fake. But finding real bugs, improving real user experience, hardening real security — those are ALWAYS real.

